<br>
Basically, if you want to know a step by step of everything that happened while there, read this: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=21804">forums.interealms.com/sha...adid=21804</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
While there I was able to corner Rytan, the Developer in charge of the upcoming PvP changes, for more than 4 hours over the two days we were there. To say we had access to the people we wanted would be a joke. We had unlimited access to everything at SOE, including the personel. The devs hung out with us everywhere we went, including getting drunk with us at the hotel bar until 4am the first night, prior to the events even begining. I even got to sit next to Jamlamin to see the new petition system(it's nice irl) implemented in the last two weeks. At noon on Saturday, the number one complaint was about Termi and Attis warping and double DTing people. It was pretty lol~ <br>
<br>
While at the GM booth, I saw the on wall projection of petition counts, population numbers, etc. We had half the population of any other server on the wall, or less. Brenlo said that was nothing new, and it had always been that way. I got Brenlo's personal assurance that he'd try to find a way to open movelogs to/from Sullon Zek, however it's quite a daunting task due to religions not being able to be changed without overhauling the entire character file, which takes about 4 man hours. We were even shown in depth how that would work, and why it was challenging. Personally, I don't see why they can't make an automated system to do the manual things, however it would take time invested into a project to do this. We'll see if it ever materializes. <br>
<br>
In the time spent with Rytan, Bakda and myself learned tons about the upcoming PvP changes. We were also able to give him ideas that will be implemented with the changes. Many of these came directly from the feedback we got on the threads I posted on guild boards. <br>
1) The water bug is gone as of now on the Test server. <br>
2) Zoning and gaining hitpoints equal to your gear is gone on Test server. <br>
3) Rogues will most likely get a structured AA for damage shield mitigation. <br>
4) Backstab will be mitigated less in PvP, raising the damage done by item on average. (This seemed promising, but he said it needed more testing) <br>
5) A PvP points system is already programmed and coming 100%. The items are already in the system as to what you can buy. When the PvP test server goes live, this will be tested as well. <br>
6) I mentioned 10 dose crimson potions and invis potions, and he thought they were both good ideas and possibly could be implemented outside of this point system as well. <br>
7) Due to Stormhammer being such a success (and cash cow) we never were able to make headway into this subject. However, I did get my point across that the service completely breaks servers that are not able to transfer characters to other servers otherwise. <br>
 We were never able to talk about class balance at all. We were fortunate enough to talk about rogue damage shield mitigation. He's aware that bards are grossly overpowered, and is already working on a fix to capping bard spells such as mana sieve. PvP balance will be tested thoroughly when the test server goes live, and I reccomend strongly you all help with it if you want your say. <br>
9) The concept of PvE level limitsbeing enforced on PvP spells kind of got brushed aside as needing more evaluation, so those of you swinging on the nuts of rapture are safe for a bit longer. <br>
10) Dispells may or may not become resistable, depending on testing. He thought it was an interesting concept and a way to make some classes better at dispelling than others, as it should be. However, dispells in PvP WILL be changed to dispell random slots instead of the top slots always. This will be a major change, and a fair one, in PVP. Instant clicks will still help, but they won't break dispell completely. <br>
11) We are getting more buff slots for us and mobs. The idea was loved by all. <br>
12) Horse fixes will go live as they are proposed on EQlive forums. Stuns will knock you off horses. Snares will snare both the horse and you. Horses will remain unkillable. <br>
13) Plane of War: Battle Zone Extraordinaire was a concept loved by everyone at the event from the ubers to the casul players. Basically, I'd look for an instancable zone to be added with an expansion in the future that allows for a NON PVP, non instanced set up spot with entrances into PvP events (ala PoJ trials) such as 3 vs 3, 1 vs 1, 6 vs 6, 18 vs, 18, 54 vs 54, king of the hill, capture the flag, etc. The bonus to this is since instanced zones are done on a server farm with all other instanced zones, we will have the ability to fight people from other servers as well. Samdaman vs Furor anyone? <br>
14) They didn't really give a shit about training. I explained to them that it's always been used as a way for teams to control each other prior to instanced zones. Withinstanced zones training is broken giving people with instanced zones an advantage over others. I explained that at present Goods and Newts don't like training, and evils use it as a means of perpetual dominance. They still didn't really care, as it's always been that way. The only way training would go away on Sullon Zek, in their opinion, was with a ruleset change. We'd also lose all of our hardcore aspect in the change and the PnP would be enforced. <br>
15) I was amazed at how open they were with me on hacking. I completely derailed a 1 hour GM 20 person session talking about hacking for 20 to 30 minutes of it. Hacking will never be completely fixed. SEQ and other passive forms of hacking that do not change in game functions will never be fixed. Other hacks, such as megawarp, /gate, /zone, Feign dead hack etc will be addressed as they can. As long as people don't do something with hacks that is physically impossible for their characters to do, and/or Gms don't witness it first hand, then they won't get busted for it. <br>
16) Melees wil be getting PvP only abilities, and they may add spells with more PvP intent, or PvP only. <br>
17) AHR bracer will be nerfed to increase cast time. Other PvP imbalancing items such as the alliance necklace will also be looked at. <br>
1 Snares, Roots, Blinds, and other similarly crippling spells will now have a new field in Lucy for PvP resists and PvP duration. Snares will not last 14 minutes when they land, instead they will land MUCH more frequently and last small durations of time. I was told someone with high MR could expect to have snare last 12 to 18 seconds, which should help greatly in combating training. <br>
19) Merging the Good and Neutral teams will never happen. The population numbers are currently NOT skewed. In reality I got to see a great breakdown of it, and they are closer now than they ever have been in sheer numbers. The major difference is in gear and average AA points/levels. Merging goods and newts will just cause an unfair imbalance another way, and breaks the original premise of the server. <br>
20) I proposed that DA type spells be able to be dispelled in PvP. They didn't know if it was such a great idea, and said they'd be willing to test it on PvP test servers. <br>
21) PvP resists are getting a MAJOR overhaul. Expect every spell to have a PvP resist and a PVE resist. They will each be tuned for PvP. Spells with Multiple resist checks will also be tuned in the same way. <br>
22) Plane of Tranquility will 100% become a PvP zone. Plane of Knowledge and Nexus are up for debate still. Bazaar will not become a PvP zone for obvious reasons. <br>
23) The ranger unNerf of archery to 80% damage will most likely go through to live servers, but will be tested on the PvP test server first. Also, rangers are already fixed on test such that they cannot shoot through walls or trees anymore. <br>
24) Unfortunately, I didn't have time to get to Gate spells being unbalanced in PVP. I will be forwarding more information to Rytan about this. It's my opinion that Gate spells should not be allowed to be modified by spell haste effects on items or spells, justlike complete heal. 3.0 second gates are overpowered. <br>
25) Didn't get to Illusions in PvP. Coding for this would take quite some effort, and we are a long way off from getting more important shit straight to have to worry about this one. <br>
26) Pets will most likely be getting a resist system similar to their owner's or a portion thereof in PvP. Also, pets and push are being looked into. Pets may not be able to push mobs at all soon, getting rid of the pushing through walls issue being uncontrollable. <br>
27) The hitbox increase was seen as a good thing at the summit and willl be going live once test on the test server. However, don't necessarily expect it to go live as a 50% increase. I'd imagine it will be tested and end up in the 20 to 30% range. <br>
2 Didn't get to discuss bards gating mobs. This would require a good bit of effort to fix, but I will be forwarding it to Rytan also. We'll just live with this one for now. <br>
29) PoK stones, the ones on theother end of them, and LDoN Magus will all have a 10 second cast time with small radius. When you click or hail them, they will begin casting. If you run out of range of them, they will stop and interrupt. <br>
30) Rez boxes and TL boxes will have a component added to them such that if you move more than a little bit with them up, they poof. This should severely limit the ability to rez box and TL box train. <br>
<br>
